The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Business Briefs
                                                                                                               Business Briefs
                              
	 Mumbai, May 17: Tata Steel has taken major retail initiatives, including doubling its outlets to 1,000 in the next two-three years for its branded products, to promote the sale of its products in the country. The company will increase the number of steeljunction outlets in the eastern region through franchises to sell all kinds of steel items such as furniture, jewellery, cutlery and home-building items and branded products.                             
	 Berlin, May 17: Volkswagen AG has called off the next round of talks over a planned integration with sports car maker Porsche SE, saying the atmosphere is not conducive for constructive discussions. The next round of talks at the working group level were scheduled for Monday, Volkswagen spokesperson Christine Ritz said.                            
	 New Delhi, May 17: Futures trading in wheat is likely to resume next week on the three national commodity exchanges  NCDEX, MCX and NMCE  after a ban of nearly two-and-a-half years. The Centre lifted the ban on wheat futures, that was imposed in February 2007, on May 15.                             
	 New Delhi, May 17: The National Stock Exchange has become the worlds largest bourse in terms of stock futures contract. Over six crore contracts have been exchanged on the bourse so far this year.                            
	 New Delhi, May 17: Ranbaxy Laboratories Ltd has chalked out plans to revamp its US business,which is faced with massive losses along with regulatory hurdles.                                                                                                                           
